examples.en: She hardly dared hope that he was alive.
She dared him to dive off the bridge.
No one dared to gainsay him.
She dared not trust such a treasure to mortal.
Only a few journalists dared to cover the story.
Few people dared to venture out during the hours of darkness.
She dared me to ask him out on a date. I did, and he said yes.
No one dared to question his decisions.
Few reporters dared to enter the war zone.
I dared not cry or show any sign of weakness.
They dared Ed to steal a bottle of his father's whiskey.
The actress dared a new interpretation of the classic role.
He dared to challenge the established (=traditional) order.
She hardly dared to understand the meaning behind his statement.
None of the students dared to talk back to the crotchety old teacher.
He had dared to speak out against injustice, and overnight he became a national hero.
